		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=RattailScoundral&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p> Here's a quote from D&amp;D: Druids are charged with the protecting wilderness-- in particular trees, wild plants, wild animals, and crops. Druids recognize that all creatures, including humans (and halflings) need food, shelter, and protection from harm. They recognize that hunting, farming, and cutting lumber are all parts of the natural cycle. However, druids will not tolerate the unnecessary destruction or exploitation of nature for profit.<br><br> Later on, D&amp;D continues: a druid's sole purpose in adventuring is to gain experience and grow stronger.<br><br> As your GMs explain, the quest is to help you grow in your hunting and gathering skills. There is no harm in killing plants or animals to grow stronger, just as those very same animals are welcome to make a meal out of any halfling they can best.<br><br> Also, killing animals for pelts or meats, in order to increase in tradeskill would be acceptable. Killing animals that give you no experience and have nothing you need- killing them for fun, basically, is bad.<br><br> I'm guessing you meant from a roleplaying aspect, so in a nutshell- killing animals, when it's progressive, is part of the cycle of life and is perfectly ok.<br><br> As a druid, your spells are aimed to give you the upper hand against animals and plants simply because you have a harmony with nature. Unfortunatally, as it turns out, this makes druids animal and plant -killing machines, ironic.<br><br> Aside from roleplaying, there are no real in-game backlashes for killing plants or animals. Some people claim there is an invisible faction for killing wolves that will make all wolves hate you, but this is a load of rubbish. As Lady deadside said, Treants are about the only thing you should avoid killing, and bears in surefall glade.<br><br> Good luck with the complex of being a nature-protector with a million anti-animal spells =/<br> </p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from a computer</td><td align="right" id="fs8" >0 Replies</td></tr></table>
